Here’s a compact PlantUML class diagram for **LCP-UML-8**:

```plantuml
@startuml LCP-UML-8
title LCP-UML-8: Multi-National Manufacturing PLM

' Core product taxonomy
class Product {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +sku: String
}
class RawMaterial
class SubAssembly
class FinishedProduct

Product <|-- RawMaterial
Product <|-- SubAssembly
Product <|-- FinishedProduct

' Structures and governance
class BillOfMaterials {
  +version: String
  +effectiveFrom: Date
}
class ChangeOrder {
  +status: String
  +priority: String
}
class ComplianceCert {
  +certType: String
  +expiry: Date
}
class SupplierContract {
  +terms: String
  +incoterms: String
}

BillOfMaterials *-- Product : contains >>
ChangeOrder --> Product : affects
ComplianceCert --> Product
SupplierContract --> RawMaterial

' Engineering design domain
class EngineeringDesign {
  +lifecycleState: String
}
class CADModel { +filePath: String }
class Drawing { +pdfPath: String }
class Revision { +revCode: String }
class Engineer { +role: String }

EngineeringDesign *-- CADModel
EngineeringDesign *-- Drawing
EngineeringDesign *-- Revision
Engineer --> EngineeringDesign : owns
ChangeOrder --> EngineeringDesign : updates

' Manufacturing execution
class ManufacturingProcess { +name: String }
class WorkCenter { +code: String }
class Machine { +assetTag: String }
class Operator { +badge: String }
class WorkOrder { +scheduleDate: Date }
class Operation { +seq: int }
class ShopFloorExecution

ManufacturingProcess *-- Operation
WorkOrder *-- Operation
WorkOrder --> Product : builds
ShopFloorExecution *-- WorkOrder
WorkCenter *-- Machine
Operation --> WorkCenter : performed at
Operator --> Operation : executes
ChangeOrder --> WorkOrder : re-plans

' Quality assurance
class QualityAssurance
class InspectionPlan { +method: String }
class InspectionResult { +status: String }
class NonConformance { +severity: String }
class CorrectiveAction { +action: String }

QualityAssurance *-- InspectionPlan
InspectionPlan *-- InspectionResult
InspectionResult --> NonConformance : triggers
NonConformance --> CorrectiveAction : resolved by
QualityAssurance --> Product : controls
ChangeOrder --> InspectionPlan : updates tests

' Logistics and traceability
class InventoryLot { +lotNo: String; +expiry: Date }
class Warehouse { +location: String }
class CustomerOrder { +orderNo: String }
class Shipment { +tracking: String }
class TraceabilityRecord { +event: String; +timestamp: Date }

InventoryLot --> RawMaterial
InventoryLot --> SubAssembly
Warehouse *-- InventoryLot
CustomerOrder --> FinishedProduct
Shipment --> CustomerOrder
TraceabilityRecord *-- InventoryLot
TraceabilityRecord --> WorkOrder
TraceabilityRecord --> InspectionResult
TraceabilityRecord --> Shipment

@enduml
```

Key notes:
- Inheritance: `Product` base with `RawMaterial`, `SubAssembly`, `FinishedProduct`.
- Composition (filled diamonds) captures ownership: e.g., `WorkOrder *-- Operation`, `EngineeringDesign *-- CADModel`.
- Cross-cutting links show governance flows: `ChangeOrder` impacts design, BOM, and work orders; `TraceabilityRecord` ties material, execution, QA, and outbound logistics.
